10/05/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan is expected to meet with US President George W. Bush on 8 June, according to a government statement.
Erdogan is scheduled to visit Washington to attend a session of the American-Turkish Council from 5 June until 7 June.
A meeting between Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul and US Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice is planned for 8 June.
(NTV - 10/05/05)
